            <section ID="id_link_2ecf321a-6077-30bd-e054-00144ff88e88">
               <id root="75b0c827-08e9-e445-e053-2991aa0a2141"/>
               <code code="34067-9" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="INDICATIONS &amp; USAGE SECTION"/>
               <title>INDICATIONS AND USAGE</title>
               <text>
                  <list listType="ordered">
                     <item>Prevention of nausea and vomiting associated with highly emetogenic cancer chemotherapy.</item>
                     <item>Prevention of nausea and vomiting associated with initial and repeat courses of moderately emetogenic cancer chemotherapy.</item>
                     <item>Prevention of nausea and vomiting associated with radiotherapy in patients receiving either total body irradiation, single high-dose fraction to the abdomen, or daily fractions to the abdomen.</item>
                     <item>Prevention of postoperative nausea and/or vomiting. As with other antiemetics, routine prophylaxis is not recommended for patients in whom there is little expectation that nausea and/or vomiting will occur postoperatively. In patients where nausea and/or vomiting must be avoided postoperatively, ondansetron tablets, USP are recommended even where the incidence of postoperative nausea and/or vomiting is low.</item>
                  </list>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20160323"/>
            </section>
         </component>
